ased","1380–Male":"1380–Deceased","about 1380":"about 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hunte","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Hunt  . This form of the surname is common in the West Indies (mainly Barbados and Trinidad and Tobago) and Guyana.","North German: habitational name from the Hunte river in Lower Saxony."],"variants":[{"name":"Hunt","meanings":["English (southwestern): occupational name for a hunter, from Middle English <i>hunte</i> ‘hunter, huntsman’ (Old English <i>hunta</i>). The term was used not only of the hunting on horseback of game such as stags and wild boars, which in the Middle Ages was a pursuit restricted to the ranks of the nobility, but also to much humbler forms of pursuit such as bird catching and poaching for food. The word seems also to have been used as an Old English personal name and to have survived into the Middle Ages as an occasional personal name. Compare   Huntington   and   Huntley  .","Irish: adopted for various Irish surnames containing or thought to contain the Gaelic element <i>fiadhach</i> ‘hunt’; for example <b>Ó Fiaich</b> (see   Fee  ) and <b>Ó Fiachna</b> (see   Fenton  ).","Possibly an Americanized form of German   Hundt  ."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Hunte was born about 1380, in Essex, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"about 1380–":"umbes 1380–Surnud","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","about 1380":"umbes 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1380–":"noin 1380–Kuollut","1410–Male":"1410–Kuollut","1380–Male":"1380–Kuollut","about 1380":"noin 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1380–":"environ 1380–Décédé","1410–Male":"1410–Décédé","1380–Male":"1380–Décédé","about 1380":"environ 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William Hunte est né environ 1380, à Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"about 1380–":"um 1380–Verstorben","1410–Male":"1410–Verstorben","1380–Male":"1380–Verstorben","about 1380":"um 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"William Hunte wurde um 1380 in Essex, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"about 1380–":"about 1380–Desede","1410–Male":"1410–Desede","1380–Male":"1380–Desede","about 1380":"about 1380","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"about 1380–":"1380 körül–elhunyt","1410–Male":"1410–elhunyt","1380–Male":"1380–elhunyt","about 1380":"1380 körül","1410":"1410","1380":"1380","Gosfilde, Essex, England":"Essex, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"about 1380–":"sekitar 1380–Telah Meninggal","1410–Male":"1410–Telah Meninggal","1380–Male":"1380–Telah Meninggal","about 1380":"sekitar 1380","1410"